{
  "texts": [
    "Performance and Efficiency Comparison inReal-World Experiment Tasks and setup.",
    "We evaluate on four manipulation tasks executed on a Franka Research 3 robot: folding a garment (Clothes), inserting a tennis ball into a box (Ball), sweeping trash into a dustpan with a brush (Brush), placing a block in the purple region (Block).",
    "Given a single RGB-D frame and a language instruction, TraceGen predicts a 3D trace, which is converted to joint commands via inverse kinematics.Baselines.",
    "We include both video-based and trace-based world models.",
    "Video-generation approaches such as AVDC [24] and NovaFlow [27] first synthesize future video and then estimate 3D motion post hoc; consistent with NovaFlow's evaluation, we use only the video-generation component of AVDC and apply a unified video-to-trace extraction pipeline across all video-based baselines."
  ]
}